OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FWhat can I do if I can't   
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fpay my energy bill?        
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Energy bills will fall significantly   
OL,6, from July but prices are still much    
OL,7, higher than they were a few years ago, 
OL,8, leaving many people worried about how  
OL,9, to pay their bills.                    
OL,11,FSome of those struggling have been     
OL,12,Fforced onto more expensive prepayment  
OL,13,Fmeters, prompting energy regulator     
OL,14,FOfgem to introduce tougher rules to    
OL,15,Fprotect consumers.                     
OL,17,FIf you don't agree a payment plan with 
OL,18,Fyour supplier, they might try to force 
OL,19,Fyou to have prepayment meter installed,
OL,20,For they may switch your existing smart 
OL,21,Fmeter to prepayment mode.              
